FINISHING sector -- dry + recover the battery-precursor Li2CO3 product.

GREEN (runnable standalone: runCase tutorials/plant/lithiumBrinePlant/FINISHING).

Two units, the natural finishing train:
  - dryer (evaporativeDryer): removes the cake's FREE surface moisture by a
    real hot-air stream.  This is a NEW engine unit, built for exactly this:
    a crystalline inorganic like Li2CO3 holds free surface water, NOT
    GAB-sorbed water, so the sorption-based solidDryer was the wrong model.
    The evaporativeDryer is the honest one -- constant-rate evaporation
    limited by the first of three declared limits (all water gone / exhaust
    air saturates / energy floor), each announced.  Adiabatic: T_out is a
    RESULT, no phantom duty.
  - recoverer (cyclone, Lapple): recovers the dried fines from the carrier
    air as product; the cut diameter follows from the gas + the Li2CO3
    crystal density (its case-local component record).

The Li2CO3 solid product record (constant/components/Li2CO3.dat, Route 2,
real public-domain crystal data) is the crystalliser's product in CARBONATION
-- ready when that sector wires the real slurry rate here.
